Shellcheck
Shellcheck is a program to debug bash scripts.
It is availible online, can also being installed.

Errors messages
Bash error masseges are broken into parts separated by colons.
First prt is a program name, remaining parts help to narrow dowm the issue
Common bash errors:
	- No such file or directiry
	- File exists
	- Permission denied
	- Operation not permitted

Finding help
There are 3 commands available for help.
	help - used nmostly for bash build-in commands
	gives short explanation what command does
	to check if command is build-in: type -a command
	man - manual page for external commands
	info - the biggest one. gives detailed explanation what command does
